@startuml 10-sequence-rag-pipeline
title RAG Pipeline — Document Ingestion & Retrieval

actor User
participant "Client / Agent" as Client
participant "Document\nIngestion" as Ingest
participant "Chunking\nService" as Chunk
participant "Embedding\nService" as Embed
participant "Metadata\nExtraction" as Meta
participant "Knowledge\nManagement" as KM
participant "Vector Search" as Search
database "PostgreSQL\n(pgvector)" as PG
database "Cloud Storage" as GCS
participant "LLM Provider" as LLM

== Ingestion Pipeline ==

User -> Client : Upload port SOP document
Client -> Ingest : POST /process\n{content, metadata}
Ingest -> GCS : store raw document
Ingest -> Chunk : POST /process\n{content, options}
Chunk --> Ingest : {chunks[]}

Ingest -> Meta : POST /process\n{content}
Meta --> Ingest : {entities, metadata}

loop For each chunk
  Ingest -> Embed : POST /process\n{content}
  Embed -> LLM : embeddings API
  LLM --> Embed : vector[1536]
  Embed --> Ingest : {embeddings}
  Ingest -> PG : INSERT document_chunks\n(embedding, content)
end

Ingest -> KM : register document
KM --> Client : {document_id, status: indexed}

== Retrieval (at query time) ==

User -> Client : "What are berth allocation rules?"
Client -> Search : POST /process\n{content: query, top_k: 5}
Search -> Embed : embed query
Embed -> LLM : embedding API
LLM --> Embed : query vector
Search -> PG : cosine similarity search\n(IVFFlat index)
PG --> Search : top-k chunks
Search --> Client : {results[], scores[]}

Client -> Client : Pass chunks to Agent as context
note right of Search
  similarity_threshold: 0.7
  max_results: 20
end note

@enduml
